                "id_policy": 8,
                "name": "Traditional to industrial agriculture",
                "definition": "This policy initiates a shift in agricultural management from traditional to industrial practices. This change will take place over the established period.  Industrial agriculture defined as high input farming based on specialization, monocultures, genetical uniformity and  mechanized systems. It is associated with negative outcomes for biodiversity and soils. Traditional agriculture is the low input farming and subsistency farming.",
