                "name": "Effect oil and gas in agriculture",
                "definition": "This policy simulated this effect on a basic way via exogenous outputs. Oil and gas are esential inputs of the agriculture of developped countries (the so call industrial agriculture in this model). The shortage of these fossil fuels might trigger a crisis:  farmers might be forced to cultivate without fossil fuel based chemical inputs such as pesticides and fertilizers (because of high prices, for example), causing a dramatic drop in agricultural yields.",
